Usage: reinforce_pg [-help] [-area {x1, y1, x2, y2}]
                    [-area_blockage {{x1 y1 x2 y2} {x1 y1 x2 y2 x3 y3 x4 y4 ...} ...}]
                    [-pattern_file <file_name>]
                    [-snap_wire_center_to_grid {default Grid}] { -pattern_map <irdrop_value pattern_name> | -write_pattern_template <file_name> | -boxes_file <file_name> | -auto_ir_fix {preroute postroute} } [ [-tile_row_column {x y} | -tile_size {x y} | -number_region <integer>] | -write_pattern_template <file_name> ] [ -rail_analysis_directory {directory} | -write_pattern_template <file_name> ]

-help                                   # Prints out the command usage
-area {x1, y1, x2, y2}                  # reinforce area (box, optional)
-area_blockage {{x1 y1 x2 y2} {x1 y1 x2 y2 x3 y3 x4 y4 ...} ...}
                                        # Specify one or multiple
                                        # rectangular/rectilinear area
                                        # blockages (string, optional)
-auto_ir_fix {preroute postroute}       # Specifies to fix irdrop with auto
                                        # flow. (enum, optional)
-boxes_file <file_name>                 # file name for boxes
                                        # (string, optional)
-number_region <integer>                # Number of regions for Voltus power
                                        # analysis
                                        # (int, optional, min=1, max=65536)
-pattern_file <file_name>               # file name for pattern template
                                        # (string, optional)
-pattern_map <irdrop_value pattern_name>
                                        # Specify the pattern for irdrop fixing
                                        # through irdrop_value and pattern_name
                                        # defined at pattern_file
                                        # (string, optional)
-rail_analysis_directory {directory}    # reinforce_pg will read the rail
                                        # analysis data under the directory
                                        # (string, optional)
-snap_wire_center_to_grid {default Grid}
                                        # Specifies snap wire center to routing
                                        # grid (enum, optional)
-tile_row_column {x y}                  # Specify the tile number for power
                                        # analysis in the x and y direction
                                        # (string, optional)
-tile_size {x y}                        # Specify the tile size for power
                                        # analysis in the x and y direction
                                        # (string, optional)
-write_pattern_template <file_name>     # Output a template of the pattern
                                        # file. (string, optional)